<li class="show">innovativer Gehalt</li>
<li class="show">politische Relevanz</li>
<li class="show">Methodikspektrum</li>
<li class="show">Adressat_innentauglichkeit</li>
</ul>',
    'en_US' => '<p><strong>Review Guidelines:</strong></p>
<p>Once a submitted paper has been assessed as suitable by the editors, the anonymised text will be read and commented by at least two external referees. The editorial team decides on the basis of these reviews about the papers acceptance, rejection or suggestions and requirements for resubmission.</p>
<p>In general, we ask reviewers to keep in mind the aims of s&nbsp;u&nbsp;b&nbsp;\\&nbsp;<strong>u&nbsp;r&nbsp;b&nbsp;a&nbsp;n</strong> in writing their evaluations and to reflect on their own positionality within the wider interdisciplinary field of urban studies.</p>
<p><br>The article should be reviewed in regards to the following criterias:</p>
<ul>
<li class="show">clear research question</li>
<li class="show">clear rationale of the thesis</li>
<li class="show">logic of argumentation</li>
<li class="show">clarity of language</li>
<li class="show">innovative content</li>
<li class="show">political relevance</li>
<li class="show">methodological approach</li>
<li class="show">matching theme and scope of the journal</li>
</ul>',
